Iâ€™m wondering whether there is a bug here. It seems to me that this is assuming that the effective value is only available when SFFO is not being used, but `COutput.effective_value` is set and aggregated whenever the COutputs have a feerate. Does this not explicitly need to handle SFFO? I.e., maybe this needs to be something along the lines of:

```suggestion
            CAmount available_coins_total_amount = coin_selection_params.m_subtract_fee_outputs ? available_coins.GetTotalAmount() : available_coins.GetEffectiveTotalAmount();
            CAmount available_effective_balance = preset_inputs.total_amount +available_coins_total_amount;
```

